  "text": "An important observation is that MU codes constructed using Dyck sequences are inherently balanced, as they contain n 2 ones and n 2 zeros. The balancing property also carries over to all prefixes of certain subsets of Dyke sequences. To see this, recall that a Dyck sequence has height at most D if for any prefix of the sequence, the difference between the number of ones and the number of zeros is at most D. Hence, the disbalance of any prefix of a Dyck sequence of height D is at most D. Let Dyck(n, D) denote the number of Dyck sequences of length 2n and height at most D. For fixed values of D, de Bruijn et al. [CITATION_1] proved that",
